==Secretary of State==
Incumbent Republican [[Secretary of State of Colorado|Secretary of State]] [[Scott Gessler]] did not run for re-election to a second term in office. He instead ran unsuccessfully for governor.<ref name=stateassembly/>

===Republican primary===
[[El Paso County, Colorado|El Paso County]] [[Clerk (municipal official)|Clerk & Recorder]] [[Wayne W. Williams]] was the Republican nominee.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.coloradostatesman.com/content/994788-williams-hopes-succeed-fellow-republican-gessler-secretary-state|title=Williams hopes to succeed fellow Republican Gessler for Secretary of State|date=April 13, 2014|accessdate=April 30, 2014|publisher=The Colorado Statesman|author=Peter Marcus}}</ref> [[Arapahoe County, Colorado|Arapahoe County]] [[County commission|Commissioner]] Nancy Doty considered running,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.denverpost.com/thespot/2013/11/25/republican-nancy-doty-secretary-stat/102943/|title=Republican Nancy Doty mulls 2014 secretary of state race|date=November 25, 2013|accessdate=July 22, 2014|publisher=The Denver Post|author=Lynn Bartels}}</ref> but decided against it.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.coloradostatesman.com/content/994552-republican-doty-won%3Ft-run-secretary-state|title=Republican Doty won’t run for Secretary of State|date=December 26, 2013|accessdate=July 22, 2014|publisher=The Colorado Statesman|author=Lynn Bartels}}</ref>

