===Democratic primary===
[[Regents of the University of Colorado|Regent]] of the [[University of Colorado]] [[Joe Neguse]] was the Democratic nominee.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.denverpost.com/thespot/2014/04/10/joe-neguse-colorado-secretary-of-state/108027/|title=Democrat Joe Neguse, son of African immigrants, runs for secretary of state|date=April 10, 2014|accessdate=April 30, 2014|publisher=The Denver Post|author=Lynn Bartels}}</ref> Former Majority Leader of the [[Colorado Senate]] and nominee for secretary of state in 2006 Ken Gordon had also declared his candidacy in December 2012,<ref name=gordonnicolais/> though it was unclear if he was continuing in the race after Neguse entered in June 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.coloradostatesman.com/content/994241-democrat-joe-neguse-files-sos|title=Democrat Joe Neguse files for SoS|date=June 27, 2013|accessdate=April 30, 2014|publisher=The Colorado Statesman|author=Peter Marcus}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.denverpost.com/thespot/2013/11/20/preseason-for-next-years-secretary-of-states-race-is-officially-underway-as-williams-name-endorsers/102800/|title=Preseason for next year’s secretary of state’s race is officially underway as Williams name endorsers|date=November 20, 2013|accessdate=April 30, 2014|publisher=The Denver Post|author=Joey Bunch}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.denverpost.com/news/ci_24778756/former-state-senate-majority-leader-ken-gordon-dies|title=Former state Senate Majority Leader Ken Gordon dies at 63|date=December 22, 2013|accessdate=April 30, 2014|publisher=The Denver Post|author1=Joey Bunch|author2=Lynn Bartels}}</ref> Gordon died of a heart attack in December 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.westword.com/latestword/2013/12/ken_gordon.php|title=Ken Gordon, lawyer, politician and crusading Coloradan, passes away|date=December 22, 2013|accessdate=April 30, 2014|publisher=Denver Westword|author=Patricia Calhoun}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ijn.com/obits/125-obits/4416-former-colorado-senate-leader-ken-gordon-dies|title=Former Colorado Senate leader Ken Gordon dies|date=January 2, 2014|accessdate=April 30, 2014|publisher=Intermountain Jewish News|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140502003437/http://www.ijn.com/obits/125-obits/4416-former-colorado-senate-leader-ken-gordon-dies|archive-date=May 2, 2014|dead-url=yes|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kdvr.com/2013/12/22/ken-gordon-former-majority-leader-dies-at-63/|title=Ken Gordon, former Majority Leader, dies at 63|date=December 22, 2013|accessdate=April 30, 2014|publisher=KDVR|author=Eli Stokols}}</ref> Former State Senator [[Angela Giron]] also considered running for the Democratic nomination,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.denverpost.com/news/ci_24756800/recalled-colorado-state-sen-giron-polls-mulls-secretary|title=Recalled Colorado state Sen. Giron polls, mulls secretary of state race|date=December 19, 2013|accessdate=April 30, 2014|publisher=The Denver Post|author=Lynn Bartels}}</ref> but she decided against it.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kdvr.com/2014/01/12/recalled-lawmaker-giron-will-stay-out-of-colo-secretary-of-state-race/|title=Recalled lawmaker Giron will stay out of Colo. Secretary of State race|date=January 12, 2014|accessdate=April 30, 2014|publisher=KDVR|author=Eli Stokols}}</ref>

