==State Treasurer==
Incumbent Republican [[Colorado State Treasurer|State Treasurer]] [[Walker Stapleton]] ran for re-election to a second term in office.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.denverpost.com/thespot/2014/03/04/walker-stapleton-treasurer-ament/106576/|title=Walker Stapleton and J.J. Ament: rivals join together|date=March 4, 2014|accessdate=April 30, 2014|publisher=The Denver Post|author=Lynn Bartels}}</ref>

===Republican primary===
Stapleton was unopposed for the Republican nomination.

{{Election box begin no change
| title = Republican primary results<ref name=coprimary/>
}}
{{Election box winning candidate with party link no change
| candidate = Walker Stapleton
| party = Colorado Republican Party
| votes = 323,862
| percentage = 100
}}
{{Election box end}}

===Democratic primary===
Former U.S. Representative and former Assistant Secretary for Intergovernmental Affairs in the [[United States Department of Homeland Security]] [[Betsy Markey]] was the Democratic nominee.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.denverpost.com/breakingnews/ci_23528477/former-congresswoman-suburban-mayor-running-colorado-treasurer|title=Betsy Markey, former congresswoman, running for Colorado treasurer|date=June 24, 2013|accessdate=April 30, 2014|publisher=The Denver Post|author=Lynn Bartels}}</ref> Pat Quinn, the outgoing Mayor of [[Broomfield, Colorado|Broomfield]], had also declared his candidacy in June 2013,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.denverpost.com/thespot/2013/06/24/patrick-quinnbroomfield-mayor-pat-quinn-enters-colorado-treasurers-race/97469/|title=Broomfield Mayor Patrick Quinn enters Colorado treasurer’s race|date=June 24, 2013|accessdate=April 30, 2014|publisher=The Denver Post|author=Lynn Bartels}}</ref> but he withdrew from the race in November 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.broomfieldenterprise.com/ci_24531705/outgoing-broomfield-mayor-pat-quinn-withdrawing-from-race|title=Outgoing Broomfield Mayor Pat Quinn withdrawing from race for state treasurer|date=November 15, 2013|accessdate=April 30, 2014|publisher=Broomfield Enterprise|author=Megan Quinn}}</ref>

{{Election box begin no change
| title = Democratic primary results<ref name=coprimary/>
}}
